cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.SY

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it deals with reinforcement learning and curriculum learning. It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves agents learning through self-play. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.RO (Robotics) as it discusses sim2real transfer tasks. The paper also involves computer vision techniques such as domain randomization, which could place it under cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, it could be categorized under cs.SY (Systems and Control) as it involves agents interacting with an environment.
